A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 25 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
2 Georgia Technology Authority, so as to provide for an annual inventory of artificial
3 intelligence usage by state agencies; to provide for annual reports of such; to provide for the
4 authority to develop and establish certain policies; to provide for related matters; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 25 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the Georgia
9 Technology Authority, is amended by revising Code Section 50-25-7.9, which is reserved,
10 as follows:
11 "50-25-7.9.
12 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'artificial intelligence' means a machine based
13 system that can, for a given set of human defined objectives, make predictions,
14 recommendations, or decisions influencing real or virtual environments. Artificial
15 intelligence systems use machine based and human based inputs to perceive real and virtual
