16 environments, abstract such perceptions into models through analysis in an automated
17 manner, and use model inference to formulate options for information or action.
18 (b) The authority shall:
19 (1) Not later than December 31, 2025, and annually thereafter, conduct an inventory of
20 all systems that employ artificial intelligence and are in use by any agency. Each
21 inventory shall include, but not be limited to, the following information for each such
22 system:
23 (A) The name of the system and the vendor, if any, that provided such system;
24 (B) A description of the general capabilities and uses of such system;
25 (C) Whether such system was used to independently make, inform, or materially
26 support a conclusion, decision, or judgment; and
27 (D) Whether such system underwent an impact assessment prior to implementation;
28 and
29 (2) Not later than December 31, 2026, develop and establish policies and procedures
30 concerning the development, procurement, implementation, utilization, and ongoing
31 assessment of systems that employ artificial intelligence and are in use by agencies. Such
32 policies and procedures shall, at a minimum:
33 (A) Govern the procurement, implementation, and ongoing assessment of such systems
34 by agencies; and
35 (B) Ensure that no such system results in any unlawful discrimination against any
36 individual or group of individuals.
37 (c) The authority shall prepare an annual report on the inventory of artificial intelligence
38 in use by agencies, as provided for in paragraph (1) of subsection (b) of this Code section.
39 Such report shall be provided to the Governor, Lieutenant Governor, and members of the
40 House of Representatives and Senate; provided, however, that the authority shall not be
41 required to distribute copies of the report but shall notify the recipients of the availability
42 of such report in the manner deemed by the authority to be most effective and efficient.
